oh-my-jeo
=========

oh-my-jeo is a derivative work of oh-my-hermes.

Upstream project : oh-my-hermes
Upstream author  : @rlaope and the oh-my-hermes contributors
Upstream source  : https://github.com/rlaope/oh-my-hermes
Upstream license : MIT License (see LICENSE)

The oh-my-hermes engine, skill catalog, command surface, plugin bundle, and
documentation corpus are inherited under the terms of the MIT License. The
original copyright notice is retained in LICENSE.

Changes made in oh-my-jeo:
  - oh-my-jeo brand identity, README, and architecture/workflow visualization
    (assets/oh-my-jeo-architecture.svg).
  - oh-my-jeo agent specification (docs/OH_MY_JEO_AGENT_SPEC.md) describing an
    independent coding-agent profile layered on the inherited contract engine.
  - Framework analysis filed to the shared llm-wiki knowledge vault.

The Python package import namespace and CLI entry point (`omj`) are retained
from upstream for binary/skill-catalog compatibility; the `omj` brand is layered
on top. See README.md ("Origin & attribution") for details.
